/* Stop any active SQL Agent jobs before running the below script 

Remember to adjust the values for the tempdb files accordingly, as not all instances have same tempd file configurations. 

It can take a long time to complete, if the tempdb is large. 

If the below script doesnâ€™t work, failover the active node in the AG group to the secondary, and then restart the sql engine on the node just been failed over. */

 

# Remember to adjust the values for the tempdb files accordingly, as not all instances have same tempdb configs, this can be found under: 
system database - tempdb -properties -files# 

  

use tempdb 
GO 
SELECT name, size 
FROM sys.master_files 
WHERE database_id = DB_ID(N'tempdb'); 
GO 
DBCC FREEPROCCACHE 
DBCC DROPCLEANBUFFERS 
DBCC FREESYSTEMCACHE ('ALL') 
DBCC FREESESSIONCACHE 
DBCC SHRINKDATABASE(tempdb, 10); 
dbcc shrinkfile ('tempdev') 
dbcc shrinkfile ('temp2') 
dbcc shrinkfile ('temp3') 
dbcc shrinkfile ('temp4') 
dbcc shrinkfile ('templog') 
GO 
